      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "POKE SALAD ANNIE (5) is progressing well claiming her 2nd career win latest, scoring by 9 lengths (17.39) at this track. Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. PUNITIVE (1) pinged the lids and led for most of the way to hold a minor placing when third and beaten 1.3 lengths (26.15) at Ballarat in a T3 Grade 7 over 450m. Will give a great sight again. DIVA'S ROSE (4) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing eighth (22.82) in a Grade 5 at Warrnambool. Speedy beginner who can find the front with a clean break from the middle of the draw. A forward showing wouldn't surprise. MAJOR QUEEN (8) was in the money last start here at this trip - likely to feature again.",
